lexing, in its search you lose peace inside yourself.\n\n- raja\n|\nQ. Why don't the British panic?A. They do, but very quietly. It is impossible for the naked eye to tell their panic from their ecstasy.\n\n- George Mikes, How to Be an Alien: A Handbook for Beginners and Advanced Pupils\n|\nDo I wither up and disappear, or do I make the best of my time left?.. He would not wither. He would not be ashamed of dying.\n\n- Mitch Albom, Tuesdays with Morrie\n|\nYou and me, we look out for each other. But I will take care of you a little extra, because I am your person, and you will always be my special horse.\n\n- Megan Shepherd, The Secret Horses of Briar Hill\n|\nOur masters have not heard the people's voice for generations and it is much, much louder than they care to remember.\n\n- Alan Moore, V for Vendetta\n|\nIt is called understanding when one accepts other’s talks of wisdom; but, where is the wisdom filled talk in this era?\n\n- Dada\n|\nThe Right Knowledge reduces pain-and-suffering, and increases happiness. If we fall short of having acquired the Right Knowledge, the faults is ours’, isn’t it?\n\n- Dada\n|\nThose who are not looking for happiness are the most likely to find it, because those who are searching forget that the surest way to be happy is to seek happiness for others.\n\n- Martin\n|\nLive, die, something else lives. The very soil humanity walks upon is built up from death. Digging into a flowerbed means digging into bones.\n\n- M. Jones, Frankie And Formaldehyde\n|\nIn proportion therefore, as the repulsiveness of the work increases, the wage decreases.\n\n- Karl Marx, The Communist Manifesto\n|\nA MOTHER is aMentor, who Over looks all your faults, a Trainer/Teacher, whoHaven't ceased in praying for you, anEndless counselor, sheRevere because she Reliable.\n\n- Wisdom\n|\nLife is a manifestation of the unified field of consciousness. Colors, beauty, pleasure and pain are its songs of creation.\n\n- Amit Ray, Beautify your Breath - Beautify your Lif